{"body": "Without knowing about this discussion, rubyduo and I have submitted a patch in Lighthouse for Object#in?, which seems like a less awkward alternative to Enumerable#include?\r\n\r\nThe Rails Core mailing list discussion is here: http://is.gd/MjQD5D\r\nThe ticket is here: http://is.gd/mTLfJv\r\n\r\nIt's slightly different from this proposal in that it works simply by calling include? on the parameter. This means it will work with an Array, Hash, String, Range, or anything else that supports include? but it won't allow an array of Regexp's.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/723604", "created_at": "2011-01-31T00:56:14Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/138#issuecomment-723604", "updated_at": "2011-01-31T00:56:14Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 138, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/BMorearty/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/BMorearty/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/BMorearty/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/BMorearty", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/BMorearty/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/BMorearty", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/BMorearty/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/32701e4c5c6d91bbbb092077f8bdd2f8?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fbe4188c0d0d914d4f54684b7b79fc726.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/BMorearty/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/BMorearty/received_events", "gravatar_id": "32701e4c5c6d91bbbb092077f8bdd2f8", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/BMorearty/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "BMorearty", "type": "User", "id": 16927, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/BMorearty/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523868a5bd3543c1510129b0"}, "id": 723604, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/138"}
